    <h3>Meal Planning Principles</h3>
    <p><strong>Batch cook grains and legumes.</strong> A pot of brown rice, lentils, or roasted vegetables on Sunday gives you building blocks for three or four meals. <strong>Use the fridge rule:</strong> if it's visible, you'll eat it. Keep prepped vegetables and healthy snacks at eye level. And remember — perfection is the enemy of good. An 80% nutritious week beats a 0% healthy week spent guilt-tripping yourself over one slip.</p>
